<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Selecting folders on left does not show items in right p]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=464&amp;p=2832#p2832"><![CDATA[
Indeed. I believe you. I just can't imagine what may be causing it - in fact mouse click should always show the folder in the right pane. Did it happen before installing Classic Shell and therefore you installed Classic Shell to fix it? You could open Classic Explorer settings, and try the Windows XP Simple navigation pane style or Vista style to see if it makes a difference. You will need to close the Explorer window and open it again for settings changes made to Classic Explorer.<br /><br />Although the fixes for the navigation pane in Classic Shell are when using the keyboard. Also try this setting: &quot;Auto-navigate to the select folder&quot;: Always.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Apr 18, 2013 12:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
