<title type="html"><![CDATA[Selecting folders on left does not show items in right pane]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=464&amp;p=2409#p2409"><![CDATA[
OS: Windows Server 2012 <br />Classic Explorer Version: 3.6.5 <br />  <br />In &quot;File Explorer&quot; selecting a directory in the left-pane with a single-click does NOT display the items in that directory in the right-pane.  I MUST double-click the directory on the left to reveal the items in the right-pane (double-click will select AND expand the directory in the left-pane, I frequently do NOT want to also expand the directory).  This is <strong>particularily annoying</strong>, especially when selecting a directory with many sub-directories. <br />  <br />&quot;Ummm... NO, I didn't need to see all the sub-directories on the left, just the directory contents on the right&quot; <br />  <br />Verified settings: <br />- Folder Options &gt; General tab &gt; Click items as follows: Double-click to open an item (single-click to select). <br />  <br />Is this a new Windows &quot;feature&quot;?  Or something not quite right in Classic Explorer? <br />  <br />Thanks! <br />  <br />   ---Jay R O<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=524">JayRO</a> — Tue Apr 02, 2013 7:43 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
